    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Clean company profiles with HubSpot and HTTP / REST API on autopilot for Enrichment\n\n**Pattern:** Data Enrichment · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nClean company profiles with HubSpot and HTTP / REST API on autopilot for Enrichment. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual enrichment is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Normalize Lead Payload → Remove Duplicate Leads → Enrich — Primary Provider → Primary Hit? → Merge Enrichment Paths → Score Enriched Records → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to data enrichment without manual effort\n- Anyone automating enrichment in sales\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Improves response time\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; HubSpot private-app token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "4f9c4063-7378-1514-3eaf-ab91f131132e",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -260
      ],
